      • deleteUser

        @RequestMapping(value="/useradmin/deleteUser",
                method=POST)
public String deleteUser(org.springframework.ui.Model model,
                                                                                                       @RequestParam
                                                                                                       String username)
        Delete a user. User can only be deleted if they have never logged in before. If administrator needs to remove access for a user that has previously logged in, the user account should just be disabled.
        Parameters:
        model - model
        username - username of user to delete
        Returns:
        page for user administration
